entries.title: Turkey is stopping oil not under Russian sanctions, raising global energy market supply concerns
entries.description: Much of the oil being held up by Turkey is Kazakh-origin and not subject to a Russian crude price cap, but shipment delays may impact the global energy market.

entries.title: Harry and Meghan hit out at 'exploitation and bribery' of UK media in new Netflix documentary
entries.description: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle hit out at what they called the "exploitation and bribery" of the British press in a new Netflix documentary released Thursday.

entries.title: FTX spokesman Kevin O'Leary says he lost his $15 million payday from crypto firm
entries.description: Kevin O'Leary made millions as an FTX spokesman, but he says he's lost it all after the bankruptcy of the crypto exchange.

entries.title: Europe’s energy grids face first major winter stress test as Arctic blast takes hold
entries.description: Temperatures across the Nordic countries and central and eastern Europe are also set to drop to close to or below freezing over the coming days.

entries.title: Tech layoffs in Southeast Asia mount as unprofitable startups seek to extend their runways
entries.description: Tech layoffs have been increasing in Southeast Asia as growth slows down. Existing investors are also pushing startups to extend their runways.
